<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The same could be said of the rotation system in its entirety(sp). Just because the more progressed guilds have a system set up amongst themselves to share the killing of specific mobs in a rotational order does not mean that other guils on the RTA have to follow that system.<br>
<br>
But yet the rotation system does work, and most of the guilds on the server work within this system. So why does it work? Because everyone knows that by respecting another guilds rotations, thier own rotations will be respected. NB knows that because they respect the rotations that BotS is on, BotS will then respect our rotations.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, the RTA rotation system on rotation mobs work.  I have no dispute over this topic.  In fact, I applaud how well it has worked so far.  How rotations work are clearly defined in a set of rules on the RTA message board.  The RTA does a good job a managing the rotations.<br>
<br>
Guilds that particpate in the RTA rotation system must abide by the stated RTA rules.  They are not allowed to come up with their own systems for the different rotation mobs.<br>
<br>
FCFS mobs are compeletly different however, they are not managed by the RTA.  There are no rules defined on the RTA message board on how to share FCFS mobs.   How the mob is shared is left to the guilds that are participating in killing a particular mob.  In most cases, the general rule of thumb for FCFS mobs is: &quot;kill it however and whenever you want, no one cares.&quot;<br>
<br>
Guilds do not have to follow the already estabilished FCFS rules that may have already been sit up by others that are participating in sharing a FCFS mob.  They can set up a new system.  If a conflict arises they can't go to the RTA, they must go to Verant and contact a GM becuase Verant is the <br>
highest level of authority on FCFS mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=milambus>Milambus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>RTA Admin</span><br>  Posts: 927<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/18/03 3:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=385>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://jakefitch.com/sig/eq/profile/fist1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I do understand the thought process about the abuse of continual teaming to speed through PoP. I also understand that those guilds that have done it by themselves will frown upon those that find it necessary to team up to kill these mobs. Though I do find it a tad funny that you all think that really has some type of effect on us. I play EQ for guild and individual advancement (and fun - can't forget that). I don't play to make the Uber guilds happy and content.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
