<br>
the reason we use rotations is to avoid heartburn, and ensure a guaranted access to *all* mobs that you 1) want to kill 2) are able to kill.<br>
<br>
rotation mobs, pre pop (except emp) offer such a meager reward per kill, that declaring a rotation for them is a necessity, because to reap the full reward from them, you must kill them 20,30+ times, to outfit your members.<br>
<br>
the tables have been turned in pop:  the rewards from a flag mob are near instantaneous.  That is, you can kill a flag mob 2, or perhaps 3 times and you have obtained the rewards from them and are able to move on.  This is fundamentally why flag mobs are not on rotation; however, the mobs themselves (as rogg explained) are identical to rotational mobs.<br>
<br>
If a provision for compromise would be made, that is: to allow teaming of flag mobs -- i would seek some sort of penalty / payment for teaming.  Much like the written rules of today that state: if you kill a rot mob with a team, your team becomes a single entity -- I feel this needs to be incorporated into the flag mobs.<br>
<br>
This is not a punishment, or a means 'to keep the man down' this is an exhange:  If you want to advance by using methods outside your current resources (your guild), then you must recieve some penalty for it.  This does not disallow teaming, nor does it encourage it - but it offers it up as a posibility in our system.<br>
<br>
I would propose (informally) that teaming up on a pop flag mob would merge the 2 (or more) teams into a single RTA recognized entity for (insert voted on time duration) amount of time, per killing of a flag mob, regarding AD, Behe, Grum.<br>
<br>
*example: (pretend the voted penalty was 2 months per flag mob defeat) If CB and VoLS merged to kill AD 2x, they would be considered an alliance for 4 months, combining forces on any and all rotational mobs they have access to.<br>
<br>
This of course, does not address the issue of temptation of moving forward, with the more advanced pop progressional flag mobs, but it is a start, regarding the compromise everyone is looking for.<br>
<br>
RTA is not designed to piss in anyone cereal, it's designed to be fair, for all.  But it's no more fair to allow 'pick and choose' alliances, while living under the protection of the RTA for all other rot mobs, than it is to deny anyone content with no options whatsoever.<br>
<br>
I am open to debate, on allowing for teaming -- however i fully believe there must be a penalty in some form when it is used - if the team is meant to be a temporary measure to advance.<br>
<br>
(i also, do not believe in grandfathering penalties, to break a spirit of the rule is not the same as breaking a rule -- i would not vote to penalize those who have teamed thus far) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.drow.org/eq/roster/view.php?Emil" target="top">Emil Sinclair</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, 65th Monk<br>
